@Kelvin 
You are addressing something very important about the data in these treemaps (what this type of graph is called).  These graphs show the allocation of funds and not how the funds have been distributed. Funding directly allocated to healthcare is shown on the graph as the “least funded,” but I wonder how many other subgroups in other categories indirectly aid healthcare?

There is a second major bill that has been in front of Congress – Build Back Better Act.  This bill has funding for healthcare and education plus more.  The White House and Congress have been negotiating the BBB Act but these talks have stalled.  What could you do to learn more about it and advance your interest in funding health care and education?
